HEADWORD: Tetrabranchiata
<hw>Tet`ra*bran`chi*a"ta</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n. pl.</pos>
<ety>[NL. See <er>Tetra-</er>, and <er>Branchia</er>.]</ety>
<fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>An order of Cephalopoda having four gills. Among
living species it includes only the pearly nautilus. Numerous genera and
species are found in the fossil state, such as Ammonites, Baculites,
Orthoceras, etc.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Tetrabranchiate</ent>⟦br⟧
